body_content.explanation: to give the effect of being; to appear to be a certain way or do a certain thing:
examples: I seem to have acquired (= have got although I don't know how) two copies of this book.
The entire room seemed to be vibrating with excitement.
I'm not sure, but the doves seem to be building a nest.
She sure seems to know what she's doing.
The accusations again the MP seem to have been conveniently ignored by the press.
